rComments: The best professor I ever studied under. Extremely knowledgeable and could always explain the material in ways we could easily comprehend. Always equipped with a plethora of axioms, one of the most common... "Mother nature is always cruel. You can never get something for nothing"

My absolute favourite professor from my time at Skule (98-03).  Scary dude, but knows the material inside out...comes to lectures with no notes and explains things better than any professor I had.  Also came to an ECE semi formal and complained that there wasn't enough (vodka) drinking.

Dmitrevsky truly is one of my favorite professors at U of T.  You need to listen to the man, you need to always use symmetry to turn integrals into multiplication, and you need to not be an idiot.  To the person who in 2004 claimed the man cannot even stand anymore: I had him in 2008 and he could stand for hours, the man is made of iron!
If I had a tenth of his knowledge I'd probably be teaching my own e&m class...

Had him back in the early 90's.  Did my thesis with him (voluntarily!).  The more seriously you take the subject the cooler he is.  If you have the balls, ask him why his attitude is what it is.  The answer might surprise you, shut you up AND make you respect him even more.  His one-liners are great and his knowledge of applied EM is deep.
